{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b4582406-7e9d-4d46-b991-f74a3c2754d2","content":"Here are the common options:\n\n## Templates\n\n| Template | Command |\n|----------|---------|\n| ASP.NET Core Web API | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| ASP.NET Core Minimal API | `dotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis` |\n| Node.js/Express | `npx express-generator` |\n| FastAPI (Python) | `pip install fastapi` |\n\n## ASP.NET Core Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `Individual` | Individual user accounts (ASP.NET Identity) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\nFor token-based auth (JWT), `Individual` or `SingleOrg` are most common. Would you like me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4bd13ab1-de49-48c0-a4c9-fe6f41ae78ab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/web development question. Let me check if there's anything in the current working directory that might provide context, but given the environment context says the directory contents are unavailable and it's not a git repository, this seems like a general knowledge question.\n\nLet me answer based on my knowledge of common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"D007:2D3FFD:1221149:1462913:69F93E1F"},"id":"1d673821-6a62-4ce5-9e33-208551e02fe6","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:35.989Z","parentId":"c075823b-0bd9-4da1-ab60-43b5af31c924"}
